Description: AIMS OS — Regular track (scientific & mathematical stack)
 Mathematical / scientific computing layer for the AIMS Regular track
 (Mathematical Sciences). This metapackage gives every AIMS student
 the SciPy ecosystem (numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn,
 sympy, scikit-learn, statsmodels, networkx, scikit-image, igraph,
 mpi4py for HPC, biopython, pytables, pygments, reportlab); the
 classic Jupyter Notebook + ipywidgets + the JupyterLab back-end libs
 (the JupyterLab UI itself is install-on-demand via `pipx install
 jupyterlab` since Debian does not yet package it; SageMath also
 install-on-demand on Trixie — see in-package notes);
 Maxima and wxMaxima for symbolic computation;
 GNU Octave with the scientific add-on modules (symbolic, statistics,
 optim, control, signal); R with the tidyverse, ggplot2, knitr and
 rmarkdown packages; the full TeX Live distribution with French,
 English, other-languages (including African hyphenation) and Arabic
 language packs, texlive-science, XeTeX and LuaTeX support, TeXstudio
 and biber for thesis writing; GeoGebra and gnuplot for geometry
 and plotting; gdb and valgrind for debugging C / C++ / Fortran
 code; and the OpenBLAS, LAPACK, FFTW, HDF5, GMP and MPFR development
 headers for compiling numerical software. black + mypy for Python
 code quality.
 .
 Coop-track students additionally install aims-os-bigdata (Big Data,
 NLP, Computer Vision, Climate, DB clients) or aims-os-security
 (cryptography, ethical hacking, forensics) on top of this metapackage.
 Both depend on aims-os-math, so installing either is enough to get
 the full stack.
 .
 PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, Keras and other rapidly-evolving ML
 frameworks (and Qiskit for the Quantum Computing course, plus
 PyArrow, Polars, DuckDB, spaCy, gensim and HuggingFace Transformers
 since Trixie does not yet package them) are deliberately NOT
 included — installation via `mamba install`
 (Miniforge3 ships in aims-os-core's chroot) or `pipx install` is
 the recommended path so students get current versions.
